body:
Subject: Re: Multiple .pinerc's spawned

Email body:

"CJR" == Colin J Raven  writes: CJR> Hey Ed? Robin? Here, here! CJR> I found something interesting while experimenting with different operating systems. I was running Pine on AIX4.0, and noticed something peculiar happening. CJR>  It seems to be spawning multiple .pinerc files, and I can't figure out why.  I thought maybe you guys had encountered this before?  I'm always looking for ways to optimize my setup, so any insights would be greatly appreciated!  Cheers, Robin --  Robin S. Socha Political Science Dept., Bonn University  main(){printf(&unix["\\021%six\\012\\0"],(unix)["have"]+"fun"-0x60);}

For what you're trying to do, forwarding doesn't work as intended. 

It seems you're trying to analyze spam emails for research purposes.  'bounce' works perfectly if you can set that up.  Another option is to save spam to a folder and report it all at once. This will allow you to analyze the spam in a more organized way.

  -chad


